ivardefs.name: device
ivardefs.desc: The device used to administer the medication (e.g. scoop, applicator, syringe).

ivardefs.name: material
ivardefs.desc: Material type of the package item.

ivardefs.name: quantity
ivardefs.desc: The number of product units the package would contain if fully loaded.

ivardefs.name: type
ivardefs.desc: A code that defines the specific type of packaging that the medication can be found in (e.g. blister sleeve, tube, bottle).

properties.desc: Information that only applies to packages (not products).
